  "name": "Avenging Flame",
  "ownership": {
    "default": 0
  },
  "type": "spell",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>As part of casting this spell, you must make a melee attack with a weapon against one creature within range, otherwise the spell fails. On a hit, the target suffers the attack's normal effects, and holy fire engulfs the target for the duration. This fire immediately deals <strong>1d6 radiant damage</strong>.</p><p>At the end of each of its turns, an affected creature must make a <strong>Constitution saving throw</strong>, ending the spell on a success or taking <strong>1d6 radiant damage</strong> on a failure. An affected creature that attacks or casts a spell before the end of its turn automatically fails the saving throw.</p><p><strong><em>At Higher Levels:</em></strong> When you cast this spell using a spell slot of 2nd level or higher, both the initial damage and the subsequent damage increase by 1d6 for each slot level above 1st.</p>",
